<td>Handmade tools and objects found in nature – <a href="/wiki/Chisel" title="Chisel">chisel</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hoe_(tool)" title="Hoe (tool)">hoe</a>, <a href="/wiki/Plough" title="Plough">plough</a>, <a href="/wiki/Yoke" title="Yoke">yoke</a>, <a href="/wiki/Reaping-hook" title="Reaping-hook" class="mw-redirect">reaping-hook</a>, grain pourer, <a href="/wiki/Barley" title="Barley">barley</a>, <a href="/wiki/Loom" title="Loom">loom</a>, <a href="/wiki/Earthenware" title="Earthenware">earthenware</a> (<a href="/wiki/Pottery" title="Pottery">pottery</a>) and <a href="/wiki/Weapon" title="Weapon">weapons</a></td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Neolithic_Revolution" title="Neolithic Revolution">Neolithic Revolution</a> - transition to <a href="/wiki/Agriculture" title="Agriculture">agriculture</a>. <a href="/wiki/Gathering" title="Gathering" class="mw-redirect">Gathering</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hunting" title="Hunting">hunting</a>, <a href="/wiki/Fishing" title="Fishing">fishing</a> and <a href="/wiki/Domestication" title="Domestication">domestication</a></td>
<td rowspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Farmstead" title="Farmstead" class="mw-redirect">Farmsteads</a></td>
<td rowspan="2">Tribes and formation of <a href="/wiki/Chiefdoms" title="Chiefdoms" class="mw-redirect">chiefdoms</a> in some Neolithic societies the end of the period</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Bronze_Age" title="Bronze Age">Bronze Age</a></td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Copper" title="Copper">Copper</a> and <a href="/wiki/Bronze" title="Bronze">bronze</a> tools, <a href="/wiki/Potter%27s_wheel" title="Potter's wheel">potter's wheel</a></td>
<td rowspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Agriculture" title="Agriculture">Agriculture</a> – <a href="/wiki/Cattle" title="Cattle">cattle</a> – breeding, <a href="/wiki/Agriculture" title="Agriculture">agriculture</a>, <a href="/wiki/Craft" title="Craft">craft</a>, <a href="/wiki/Trade" title="Trade">trade</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Iron_Age" title="Iron Age">Iron Age</a></td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Iron" title="Iron">Iron</a> tools</td>
<td>Formation of <a href="/wiki/City" title="City">cities</a></td>
<td>Formation of <a href="/wiki/Sovereign_state" title="Sovereign state">states</a>*</td>
</tr>
</table>
<ul>
<li>Formation of states starts during the Early Bronze Age in Egypt and Mesopotamia and during the Late Bronze Age first empires are founded.</li>
</ul>
